<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910924-0133</DOCNO><DOCID>910924-0133.</DOCID><HL>   Bell Atlantic in Joint Venture</HL><DATE>09/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   BEL SFA</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)TELEPHONE SYSTEMS, INCLUDING CELLULAR (TLS)</IN><NS>JOINT VENTURES (JVN)</NS><RE>GEORGIA (GA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   PHILADELPHIA -- Bell Atlantic Corp. and Scientific-AtlantaInc. said they formed a joint venture to market aninformation management system for electric utilities in theU.S. and overseas.   The companies declined to disclose terms of thetransaction.</LP><TEXT>   The integrated, two-way information management systemwould allow electric power companies to monitor usage,voltage, outages and the status of such devices as capacitorbanks at the customer level.   A spokesman for Scientific-Atlanta, which will provide thehardware, said the system will cost about $450 per point, ormonitoring station.   Bell Atlantic is a regional Bell telephone company.Scientific-Atlanta, based in Atlanta, makestelecommunications equipment.</TEXT></DOC>